info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 06 at 5:16PM PST until January 06 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM THIS EVENING... ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON SATURDAY TO 4 AM SUNDAY... * WHAT...For the first Wind Advisory, south winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 60 mph. For the second Wind Advisory, southeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Del Norte Interior and Northern Humboldt Interior Counties. * WHEN...For the first Wind Advisory, until 7 PM this evening. For the second Wind Advisory, from noon Saturday to 4 AM Sunday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS... Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
